    • Method Detail

      • doCreate

        public CommandSubstituteMethod doCreate(java.lang.reflect.Method method,
                                        ParameterSpec<io.spine.core.CommandEnvelope> parameterSpec)
        Description copied from class: MethodSignature
        Creates the HandlerMethod instance according to the passed raw method and the parameter specification.

        By implementing this method descendants define how the parameter spec is used to fit the Message envelope onto the parameter list during the method invocation.

        This method is designed to NOT perform any matching, but rather create a specific instance of HandlerMethod.

        Specified by:
        doCreate in class MethodSignature<CommandSubstituteMethod,io.spine.core.CommandEnvelope>
        Parameters:
        method - the raw method to wrap into a HandlerMethod instance being created
        parameterSpec - the specification of method parameters
        Returns:
        new instance of HandlerMethod

      • skipMethod

        protected boolean skipMethod(java.lang.reflect.Method method)
        Determines, if the given raw method should be skipped as non-matching.

        Such an approach allows to improve performance by skipping the methods, that a priori cannot be qualified as message handler methods, such as methods with no required annotation.

        Overrides:
        skipMethod in class MethodSignature<CommandSubstituteMethod,io.spine.core.CommandEnvelope>
        Parameters:
        method - the method to determine if it should be inspected at all
        Returns:
        true if this method should be walked through further examination, false otherwise
        Implementation Note:
        This method distinguishes Commander methods one from another, as they use the same annotation, but have different parameter list. It skips the methods which first parameter is NOT a Command message.
